node.text: In this video, I talk about how to listen without giving feedback and I answer a few Q&A’s.

node.title: Listening Without Offering Feedback and Q&A

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Friends can be great listeners, but they are not your therapist. Your family members can be good at helping sorting through problems, but they are not therapists. You can have healthy supports and a therapist because a therapist does not operate in the same role as the other people in your life. The therapy process is unique to your needs, all about you, and offers an evidence-based perspective on healing, evolving, crisis management, and mental/emotiona health. @NEDRATAWWAB WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Talking to a friend/family member is not the same as talking to a therapist. There are unique qualities that we get from each of our relationships. With therapists, you get a one-on-one space devoted to you. 

Sometimes we expect the people in our lives to be mental health professionals. 

Know when to seek professional help or support. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Familv is not solely by blood; it's also: @NEDRATAWWAB The people who choose you The people who you feel deeply connected to The people who lovingly hold you accountable The people who offer you a sense of safety The people who consistently show up for you The people who are willing to give you what you need The people who know you well and love you greatly www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
You can't choose your biological family, but you can select what family looks like for you--friends, blood relatives, mentors, etc. 

Do you have chosen family? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Ways to Respond When You Don't Want to Gossip @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Gossiping can be a habit or a way to connect to others. To shift your behavior, work on changing the topic and letting others know that you are not interested in gossiping. 

In this post, gossip is defined as malicious, harmful, or damaging talk against another person. 

#nedranuggets

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"It's not my place to discuss someone else's life." @nedratawwab www.ncdratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"I don't want to contribute to saying anything negative about the situation." @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 18, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '"I'd rather talk about myself than talk about other people." @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Peace Hack Stop sharing with people who offer unsolicited feedback if you don't want to hear their opinion. Sometimes the boundary with yourself is selecting what you share, particularly with people who disrespect your boundaries around offering unsolicited feedback. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
You can't change people, but you can choose what you share. If you don't want unsolicited advice, establish a boundary. When your boundary is repeatedly disrespected, stop sharing. 

Self-boundary, stop sharing. 

#nedranuggets #setboundariesfindpeace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
Today marks six months since Set Boundaries, Find Peace entered the world. 

New York Times Bestseller. 
One hundred thousand copies sold. 
Six editions. 
31 translations. 
The companion workbook, The Set Boundaries Workbook, out 12/14

Thankful isn't enough to describe my appreciation for this book and the profound impact it's having on so many people. 

Set Boundaries, Find Peace resonates with us because we need permission to explore boundaries within ourselves and with others. 

We needed permission to say the hard things without apologizing for our needs. 

We needed to know that other people deal with many of the same issues. 

We needed to hear that it's healthy and reasonable to have boundaries. And that being boundaried doesn't negate you being a kind person. 

I'm honored to be the messenger. 

Dress @freepeople
Makeup @shajarazade @thevogueroom 
📸 @rltphoto_clt 
Set Boundaries, Find Peace (me)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Some people lack the self-awareness to see when they are the cause of their issues with others. Even when it might seem obvious to you, they may be oblivious to the source of the problem in their life. Using your time to convince people to see what they are unwilling to see takes a considerable about of energy. Growth is evident in your ability to let go of trying to persuade people to see what you already know. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
The ability to see yourself requires desire and openness. When people are unwilling to see themselves, you can't create their desire or make them open to the process. 

See them and decide if convincing them is worth your energy or if you want to conserve your energy. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Never deny someone's pain because you didn't mean it. 
Stop telling people, "I didn't mean to hurt you.," when they express that they're hurt. 

Accept that you can unintentionally hurt others. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This might be hard to hear, but: There are typically two reasons people don't answer their phones That don't want to talk 2.They are unavailable Respect both @NEDRATAWWAB WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
People have the right to be unavailable, and they have the right not to answer when they don't want to talk. 

Respect boundaries.

#nedratawwab #setboundariesfindpeace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Relationship maturity is looking at the whole person, good and bad, and determining based on who they are if you want to be in a relationship with them @NEDRATAWWAE WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
One of these best parts of adulthood good is choosing how you want to live. You can decide what you're willing to deal with or not. 

We can't change people. You either like who they are, or you don't like who they are. 

Ask yourself:
If I can't change anything, is this what I want? 
Can I tolerate the things that bother me about the person?
Are the flaws deal breakers?
What am I willing to accept? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: Trying to understand why something happened might get in the way of you responding and healing from what happened- knowing why is secondary to you taking action. Years will pass, and you may not know why. Feel what you need to without getting to the bottom of things. Heal without putting together the missing pieces. Repeat After Me: My part is responding to what happened, not immediately filling in the missing pieces, trying to understand why me or why this. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Perhaps knowing why will give you comfort, but it will never erase what happened. As you gather more information, respond to what you already know. 

Your power is in choosing how you want to respond. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Things to let go of: people who have let go of you how things should be controlling others redoing the past predicting the future convincing people to be like you stuff that no longer works Make room for more by releasing things you can't control or change. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Practice releasing as a way to welcome new things in things into your life. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist in Charlotte, North Carolina. May be an image of text.

node.text:
For many of us, it takes time before we are willing to accept things that we want to be different. 

With acceptance there is peace because you are no longer fighting reality. If there is something that you struggle to accept, figure what’s within your control and develop strategies to manage what you can. 

#nedranuggets
